==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionCreateLengthArc''' tool creates an arc length dimension.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateLengthArcExample.png|300px]]
{{Caption|On the right the created dimension}}

==Usage==

# Select a single circular arc.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* {{Version|1.0}}: If the {{MenuCommand|Dimensioning tools}} [[TechDraw_Preferences#Dimensions|preference]] is set to {{Value|Single tool}} (default): press the down arrow to the right of the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_Dimension.svg||x16px]][[Image:Toolbar_flyout_arrow.svg|x16px]]}} button and select the {{MenuCommand|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateLengthArc.svg|16px]] Create Arc Length Dimension}} option from the dropdown.
#* If this preference has a different value (and in {{VersionMinus|0.21}}): press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateLengthArc.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionCreateLengthArc|Create Arc Length Dimension]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Dimensions → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionCreateLengthArc.svg|16px]] Create Arc Length Dimension}} option from the menu.
# An arc length dimension is created.


